{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/updatedocs","identifier":"ReflowDocumentationPaths","question":"Does ReflowDocumentationPaths require files to be inside a valid Go module/package directory, and if so what non-source module files or directory layout are needed when running it on a temporary copy of a package directory?","answer":"Yes. `ReflowDocumentationPaths` is path-oriented, but it still loads each target as a Go package inside a Go module.\n\nDocumented/implementation facts:\n\n- It accepts either:\n  - a directory, processed non-recursively, or\n  - an individual `.go` file.\n- For each target package directory, it calls `gocode.NewModule(absDir)`.\n- `gocode.NewModule` requires an enclosing `go.mod`; it finds the nearest `go.mod` starting from the given path.\n- It then computes the package directory relative to that module root and calls `LoadPackageByRelativeDir`.\n- Therefore, a temporary copy of just `somepkg/*.go` with no enclosing `go.mod` is not enough.\n\nMinimum temp layout:\n\nIf the copied package is the module root:\n\n```text\n/tmp/reflow-copy/\n  go.mod\n  a.go\n  b.go\n```\n\nThen call `ReflowDocumentationPaths([]string{\"/tmp/reflow-copy\"}, ...)` or with individual files.\n\nIf preserving a subdirectory package:\n\n```text\n/tmp/reflow-copy/\n  go.mod\n  internal/updatedocs/\n    a.go\n    b.go\n```\n\nThen call it on `/tmp/reflow-copy/internal/updatedocs` or files inside that dir.\n\nThe `go.mod` can usually be minimal, e.g.:\n\n```go\nmodule example.com/tmpcopy\n\ngo 1.22\n```\n\nBut if the copied package imports module-local packages using the original module path, or Go package loading needs those imports to be resolvable, you may need one of:\n\n1. Preserve the original module path in `go.mod`, e.g. `module github.com/codalotl/codalotl`.\n2. Copy any imported local package directories needed by the package.\n3. Include relevant `replace` directives.\n4. Include `go.sum` if dependency resolution/downloads require it.\n\nWhat is known from the code: `go.mod` and a valid package directory layout are required. What is not guaranteed by `ReflowDocumentationPaths` itself: that a package directory copied in isolation with arbitrary imports will load successfully without the surrounding module graph/files."},{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/updatedocs","identifier":"ReflowDocumentationPaths","question":"When called with a list of package directory paths and dryRun=true, are the returned modifiedFiles paths absolute file paths under those input directories, or can they be relative/basenames? Also are failedIdentifiers annotated with package/file path, or only identifier names?","answer":"`modifiedFiles` are absolute file paths, even with `dryRun=true`.\n\nEvidence:\n- `ReflowDocumentationPaths` resolves each input with `filepath.Abs`.\n- For directory targets, it records snapshots by `f.AbsolutePath`.\n- Diffs are recorded into `modifiedSet[absPath]`.\n- The dry-run path still records the diff before restoring file contents.\n\nSo for package directory inputs, returned `modifiedFiles` should be absolute paths to changed `.go` files in those package directories, not basenames or relative paths. `dryRun` only controls restoration of contents, not path formatting.\n\n`failedIdentifiers` are not annotated with package or file path.\n\nEvidence:\n- Failures are stored in `failedSet := map[string]struct{}{}` with comment `identifier -\u003e exists`.\n- The function adds failures as `failedSet[id] = struct{}{}` from `ReflowDocumentation`.\n- `ReflowDocumentation` returns the raw identifier strings it was given/mapped from snippets.\n\nThose identifiers may have gocode’s identifier syntax, e.g. method names like `*T.Method`, field paths like `MyType.Field`, or package-doc identifiers such as `package` / possibly `package:foo.go`, but `ReflowDocumentationPaths` does not add package directory or file path context. Also, because it uses a set keyed only by identifier string, identical failed identifiers across multiple input packages would be collapsed."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1780609825,"paths":["internal/updatedocs/apply_line_edits.go","internal/updatedocs/apply_line_edits_test.go","internal/updatedocs/block_formatting.go","internal/updatedocs/block_formatting_test.go","internal/updatedocs/doc.go","internal/updatedocs/eol_vs_doc.go","internal/updatedocs/eol_vs_doc_test.go","internal/updatedocs/functions.go","internal/updatedocs/package_docs.go","internal/updatedocs/parse_snippet.go","internal/updatedocs/parse_snippet_test.go","internal/updatedocs/reflow.go","internal/updatedocs/reflow_documentation.go","internal/updatedocs/reflow_documentation_test.go","internal/updatedocs/reflow_test.go","internal/updatedocs/remove.go","internal/updatedocs/remove_test.go","internal/updatedocs/types.go","internal/updatedocs/types_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_functions_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_generics_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_package_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_types_test.go","internal/updatedocs/update_documentation_values_test.go","internal/updatedocs/values.go"],"git_clean":true,"git_commit":"022a1982830d30afa7e9c9482290206ae6a7a4d4","git_merge_base":"4c23c1dc1b99ae4eef6476b78b40fd2108f7f751"}}